Thank you for downloading FLAIM! This file explains how to install
FLAIM's pacct-format log parsing module.

-----------

1. From the directory containing the module sources, run ./configure.

   /pacct-flaim> ./configure

   This will prepare a Makefile for you.

   Note that if you specified a nonstandard installation directory for
   FLAIM-Core using the --prefix option, you will need to specify the
   same options here or the -m flag will not work when using
   FLAIM. See the FLAIM-Core installation instructions and the FLAIM
   user's manual for details on --prefix and the -m flag.

2. Run make to build the module.

   /libpacct-flaim> make

3. Run make install to install the module.

   /libpacct-flaim> make install

   The module will install to the appropriate subdirectory of
   $(prefix)/flaim. You may change this location by modifying
   the prefix variable in step 1; however, see the FLAIM user's manual
   and FLAIM-Core installation instructions before doing so.
